  "texts": [
    "The proposal distribution used gives the same non-zero probability for each possible single edge addition or deletion, and one of these changes is randomly selected.",
    "The acceptance condition always accepts a change that increases the posterior probability of the DAG, but may reject the change if it decreases the posterior probability.",
    "The more the posterior probability decreases, the more likely the change is to be rejected.",
    "A concern with MC 3 is slow convergence to the stationary distribution, a problem known as slow mixing.",
    "Eaton and Murphy (2007) therefore proposed a Hybrid MCMC foot_4 algorithm that uses an exact score-based algorithm, Dynamic Programming (see Sect.4.3.1), to develop a global proposal distribution."
  ],
